<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN"
        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
<html>
<head>
<meta http-equiv="Content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
<title>Hello, Congress.</title>
<script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.3.1/jquery.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
<%= render :partial => "shared/javascripts" %>
<link rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="Top 25 Priorities at White House 2" href="http://whitehouse2.org/priorities/top.rss">
<style>
body {
	margin: 10px 0px 20px 20px;
}
#headline {
	font-size: 9em; 
	font-weight: bold; 
	line-height: 1em;
}
#subheadline {
	margin: 5px 0px 0px 10px;
}
#hp_search_box {
	margin-top: 20px;
}
#hp_search {
	font-size: 2em;
}
#hp_search_button {
	font-size: 2em;
	border-right: solid 1px #BBB;
	border-bottom: solid 1px #BBB;	
	background-color: #DDD;
	font-weight: bold;
	color: #000;
	padding: 2px 4px 2px 4px;	
}
#hp_search_links {
	margin-top: 18px;
}
#wh2_box {
	width: 300px;
	margin-top: 30px;
}
#intro_box {
	width: 300px;
	margin-top: 30px;
	float: right;
	position: relative;
	right: 300px;
}
</style>

</head>
<body>
<div id="headline">HELLO, CONGRESS.</div>
<div id="subheadline">We're your constituents, and we're here to serve <i>you</i>.
	
	<div id="container">
	<div id="hp_search_box">
	<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
	<form action="/legislators/search" method="GET">
	<tr>
	<td valign="middle"><input type="text" id="hp_search" name="q" autocomplete="off" title="Not sure who represents you?  Just put in your address or zip code."></td>
	<td valign="middle" style="padding-left: 5px;">
		<input type="submit" value="Search" id="hp_search_button">
	</td>
	</tr>
	</form>
	</table>
	<div id="hp_search_links">
		Type a legislator's name into the box, or put your address in and we'll figure it out.  <a href="http://<%= BASE_URL %><%= url_for legislators_url(:only_path => true) %>">Complete list of legislators</a>
	</div>	
	</div>
	

	<div id="intro_box">
		At <b>Hello Congress</b>, every Senator and Representative gets their own site where their staff can request research, search our briefing room of over 2000 documents and talking points, and track the priorities of their constituents in one simple dashboard.
		<p>
	</div>

	<div id="wh2_box">
	<a href="http://whitehouse2.org/">White House 2</a> is a bipartisan network of over 8,000 citizens imagining how the White House might work if it was run completely democratically by thousands of people over the internet.  <a href="http://whitehouse2.org/signup">All U.S. citizens can join.</a>
	<p>
	<div align="center">
	<a href="http://whitehouse2.org/"><%= image_tag "wh2-logo.png", :border => 0 %></a>
	</div>		
	<p>We're setting <a href="http://whitehouse2.org/priorities/top">priorities</a>, collaborating on policy, and creating a massive database of <%= link_to "talking points", :controller => "briefing" %> covering all sides of every important issue facing our country.
	<p>
	</div>
	
	</div>
	

</body>
</html>